body:
@josevalim, I get it that the point is moot. But with your proposed approach us 'customizers' are still gonna end up with dead weight in our bundle due to the `rails.gemspec` dependencies that we're not loading. 

Plus there was this off-hand 'flimsy' remark that reflects a viewpoint that I'm curious to understand. But apparently I'm persona non-grata (on this issue, at least. @radar -- I sincerely hope I didn't earn a spot in your kill-file for bulldogging you on such a simple little thing). So I'll drop it. 

'Rough consensus and running code' is good enough for Linux, and that's worked out pretty well so far. I s'pose it's good enough for Rails.
